\begin_layout Standard
The most important operator in Prela is the 
\emph on
relational composition
\emph default
 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
r.select(s)
\end_layout

\end_inset

 which is equivalent to the relational algebra expression 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi_{r.1,s.2}(r\bowtie_{r.2=s.1}s)$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $r.i$
\end_inset

 indicates the 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

-th column of 
\begin_inset Formula $r$
\end_inset

.
 Intuitively,
 relational composition generalizes function composition in the same way (binary) relations generalize functions:
 the composition 
\begin_inset Formula $g\circ f$
\end_inset

 is sometimes written 
\begin_inset Formula $f;g$
