status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
r.eq(v)
\end_layout

\end_inset

 which returns all rows of 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
r
\end_layout

\end_inset

 whose right column equals 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
v
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
 Other filter operators like 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
.gt()
\end_layout

\end_inset

 (greater than),
 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
.lt()
\end_layout

\end_inset

 (less than),
 and 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
.rx(regex)
\end_layout

\end_inset

 (regular expression match) work the same way.
 There is also a generic 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
