\end_layout

\end_inset

 operator that filters 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
r
\end_layout

\end_inset

 by any boolean function 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
p
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
 Going back to the example,
 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
keyword.eq("character-name-in-title")
\end_layout

\end_inset

 returns rows in 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
keyword
\end_layout

\end_inset

 (which maps a movie to its keywords) such that the keyword is 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

character-name-in-title
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

;
 the expression 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
company.s(country).eq("[us]")
\end_layout

\end_inset

 first composes 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
company
\end_layout

\end_inset

